Use posix_spawn for OpenSSH client helpers that immediately exec.

Unlike ssh -f/ControlPersist/~&, these paths do not need to preserve the
caller's live address space. Ordered file actions retain native descriptor,
environment, identity-reset, signal-default, and wait-status behavior without
fork-specific application branches. closefrom is an ordered spawn action so
helpers cannot inherit unrelated low or high virtual descriptors.

